hView — visible when match phase is `complete`. Clicking calls `createMatch` with the same tier and the player's original side choice. Creates a new open match in the lobby — the opponent must find and join it manually (no forced rematch). Button text: \"Play Again\". Reuses the existing `createMatch` context action. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds.\n\n**Phase 2: Validation & Cleanup**\n- [ ] [test] Validate carry-forward invariants against post-004 code — read and verify: (a) `vrf_request_key` is stored on `CoinflipMatch` state and now emitted in `MatchSettled` event, (b) `from_randomness()` in `shared/src/constants.rs` is pure deterministic (same byte → same side, every time), (c) `timeout_cancel` uses `shared::timeout::is_expired()` + `shared::vrf_orao::is_fulfilled()` guard, (d) `join_match` rejects non-WAITING phase, `claim_payout` rejects `claimed==true` (idempotency), (e) `create_match` calls `shared::pause::check_not_paused()`, VRF unfulfilled → claim rejects. Log each finding with file:line evidence in `docs/specs/001-coinflip/history.md`. Verify: all bankrun tests pass.\n- [ ] [frontend] Remove dead code — delete unused `buildCreateMatchInstruction` export from `chain.ts` (only `buildCreateMatchTx` is used). Remove stale \"Simplified match type for UI/mock mode\" comment from `types.ts`. Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass.\n- [ ] [docs] Update spec artifacts — refresh `gap-analysis.md`: replace all MagicBlock VRF / `resolve_match` references with Orao / 3-tx-flow architecture, update test counts to current (26 coinflip + 5 platform bankrun tests), mark resolved gaps. Mark resolved carry-forward items in `checklist.md`. Update `history.md` with Phase 2 refinement entry.\n- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for coinflip pages. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures from tier name/amount changes. Then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate:\n  - **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent, only expected areas changed) → commit updated baselines\n  - **REVIEW** (changes look plausible but unexpected areas also changed, or uncertain) → do NOT commit baselines. Save the diff images from `test-results/` to `docs/specs/001-coinflip/visual-review/`, describe concerns in `history.md`, output `<blocker>Visual review needed: [describe what looks off]</blocker>`\n  - **FAIL** (layout broken, elements missing, clearly wrong) → fix the code, do NOT update baselines\n\n### Scope Decisions\n\n- **Tiers**: On-chain canonical (Iron→Diamond, 0.005→1.0 SOL). Game-engine types.ts to be aligned (Phase 2 item). Rename \"emerald\" → \"platinum\" platform-wide.\n- **Side discriminants**: 0/1 canonical (heads=0, tails=1).\n- **VRF**: Orao integration complete (spec 004). Mock-vrf feature for bankrun tests. 3-tx flow: create→join(+VRF request)→claim(+VRF read+settle).\n- **Platform program**: Included with CPI for player profile updates on settlement.\n- **Fairness verification**: Event-based approach — MatchSettled event (with randomness + vrf_request_key) + Orao randomness account lookup. No match PDA persistence needed.\n- **Deferred**: Audio integration (all 4 FR-8 items → dedicated audio spec), estimated wait time (FR-6.5 → requires match fill-rate analytics infrastructure).\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nEach checklist item is one autonomous iteration (`claude -p` invocation). The agent:\n1. Reads this spec + history.md for prior context\n2. Implements the next unchecked item\n3. Runs the verification command specified in the item\n4. If verification passes → checks the box, commits, outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n5. If verification fails → outputs `<blocker>description</blocker>` and exits\n\n**Only when ALL items are checked, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n","numLines":279,"startLine":1,"totalLines":279}}}
